By Ojonugwa Felix Ugboja ABUJA (Sundiata Post) The 2019 presidential debate organised by the Nigeria Elections Debate Group (NEDG) and the Broadcasting Organisations of Nigeria (BON) has commenced at the Congress Hall, Transcorp Hilton, Abuja. The candidates in attendance are Fela Durotoye of the Alliance for New Nigeria (ANN), Oby Ezekwesili of the Allied Congress Party of Nigeria (ACPN) and Kingsley Moghalu of the Young Progressives Party (YPP) President Muhammadu Buhari, candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC), is conspicuously absent. Atiku Abubakar, candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) was spotted outside the venue of the debate but hasnâ€™t been seen inside the hall as at the time of writing this story.